Tautologies using standard form (north vs. south)




ST

VU




Parameters:\(x\), \(y\), \(\zeta\), \(\alpha\), \(\lambda\)
\[\begin{equation*}
x=\frac{S}{S + T} \text{, }y=\frac{U}{U + V}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\zeta=\frac{U + V}{S + T}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\alpha=\frac{S + U}{S + T + U + V}=\frac{x + y \zeta}{\zeta + 1}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\lambda=\frac{S + V}{S + T + U + V}=\frac{x + \zeta \left(1 - y\right)}{\zeta + 1}
\end{equation*}\]

Tautologies using hybrid form (west vs. east)




SU

TV




Parameters: \(g\), \(h\), \(\Gamma\), \(\alpha\), \(\Omega\) \[\begin{equation*}
g=\frac{S}{S + V} \text{, } h=\frac{U}{T + U}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\Gamma=\frac{T + U}{S + V}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\alpha=\frac{S + U}{S + T + U + V}=\frac{\Gamma h + g}{\Gamma + 1}
\end{equation*}\] \[\begin{equation*}
\Omega=\frac{S + T}{S + T + U + V}=\frac{\Gamma \left(1 - g\right) + g}{\Gamma + 1}
\end{equation*}\]

Tautologies using opposition form (upper diagonal vs. lower diagonal)




